1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,600
Welcome to this presentation on the Bring
Your Own Key feature in Copilot CLI.

2
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:22,200
BYOK stands for Bring Your Own Key,
allowing users to manage their encryption
keys.

3
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:33,300
Using BYOK gives you full control over
encryption keys.

4
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:47,200
Setting up BYOK involves three steps:
generating a key, configuring the CLI, and
verifying the setup.

5
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:06,200
The first step is to generate an
encryption key using your preferred key
management tool.

6
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:24,000
Next, update the Copilot CLI configuration
file to use the generated key.

7
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:43,100
Finally, verify the setup by running the
provided command.

8
00:01:56,100 --> 00:02:00,100
Copilot CLI also supports local models
hosted on your infrastructure.

9
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:19,100
In summary, BYOK enhances security and
compliance by giving you full control over
encryption keys.
